{"id":14880888,"mediaExerciseId":"0271f5cd-c010-424a-a9d1-757e1770f523","exerciseName":"2","chapterName":"5","chapterTitle":"Introduction to Valuation:The Time Value of Money","groupId":612291,"groupTitle":"Work The Web","isPremium":true,"sectionName":"5.3","sectionTitle":"More about Present and Future Values","pageNumber":144,"solutions":[{"id":6357731,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will use a future value calculator to determine the future value of a current investment. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The future value of an investment is the future value of the current investment up to a given date based on a given rate. This can be solved using this formula:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Future value}&=\\text{Present value} \\times (1+\\text{rate})^\\text{time}\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"However, since we are given a calculating software, we can simply substitute the time as 40 years, rate at $10.8\\%$ and present value of $\\$8,000$. This will give us:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Future value}&= \\$589,996.97\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThis means that the current investment of $\\$8,000$ will yield $\\$589,996.97$ after 40 years with the given rate. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"1bcae818-6467-44eb-b352-6626527df1e9","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd2